        question: "What access do you need to my Airbnb account?",
        answer: "We need to be added as a co-host through Airbnb's official co-host feature. This gives us permission to manage your calendar, communicate with guests, and handle bookings - but you remain the primary host and account owner. You can remove our access anytime."
      },
      {
        question: "How do payments work with co-hosting?",
        answer: "Airbnb pays you directly as usual. At the end of each month, we send you an itemized invoice for our co-hosting percentage plus any reimbursable expenses (cleaning, maintenance, etc.). You can pay via ACH, check, or credit card."
      },
      {
        question: "Can I switch between co-hosting tiers?",
        answer: "Yes! You can upgrade or downgrade your co-hosting tier anytime with 30 days notice. Many hosts start with Guest Communication and upgrade to Operations Support as they get busier. We make it easy to scale support as your needs change."
      }
